The Biden-Harris Administration is committed to supporting Puerto Rico's recovery and renewal. They have unlocked billions of dollars in disaster funding and enacted expansions of economic and healthcare assistance programs for Puerto Rico. The administration has made historic investments in Puerto Rico's infrastructure, transportation, clean water, and internet access. They have also hosted the Puerto Rico Economic Dialogue to advance commitments to Puerto Rico's growth. The administration has delivered unprecedented relief and made lasting investments for Puerto Rico's families, workers, municipalities, and businesses. They have expanded access to federal resources for rural communities and prioritized the well-being of Puerto Rico's children and families. The administration has protected communities from environmental, health, and geological threats and invested in major public infrastructure projects. They have put Hurricane Fiona disaster response funds to work and maximized and streamlined disaster recovery funds. Additionally, they have accelerated the construction of a clean, resilient, and affordable energy grid in Puerto Rico.